---
import GuideLayout from '../layouts/GuideLayout.astro';
import { SITE_NAME, SITE_URL } from '../lib/seo';
---

<GuideLayout
  title="Terms of Use - UK Salary and Tax Calculator Website"
  description="Terms of use for our free UK salary and tax calculators. All figures are estimates based on official HMRC rates for 2026/27. Not financial or tax advice."
  slug="/terms/"
>
  <h1>Terms of Use</h1>
  <p><em>Last updated: June 2026</em></p>

  <p>
    Welcome to <strong>{SITE_NAME}</strong> ({SITE_URL}). By accessing and using this website, you agree
    to be bound by the following terms and conditions. If you do not agree with any part of these terms,
    please do not use this website. These terms are governed by the UK General Data Protection Regulation
    (UK GDPR), the Data Protection Act 2018, and the Privacy and Electronic Communications Regulations
    2003 (PECR).
  </p>

  <h2>1. Purpose of the Website</h2>
  <p>
    {SITE_NAME} is an independent information platform providing free online tools for calculating
    take-home pay, income tax, National Insurance contributions, student loan repayments, pension
    contributions, and other PAYE-related estimates for the United Kingdom. The website also publishes
    informational guides about the UK tax system. All tools and content are provided for informational
    and educational purposes only and do not constitute professional tax, legal, or financial advice.
  </p>

  <h2>2. Estimates Only</h2>
  <p>
    All calculations on this site are <strong>estimates</strong> based on standard PAYE rules and HMRC
    published rates for the current tax year. Your actual take-home pay may differ due to factors
    including but not limited to: benefits in kind, employer-specific pension arrangements, overtime,
    bonuses, HMRC adjustments to your tax code, Scottish or Welsh income tax rates, and self-assessment
    obligations. Tax legislation is subject to frequent amendments, and individual circumstances can
    affect actual outcomes.
  </p>

  <h2>3. Not Financial Advice</h2>
  <p>
    <strong>This website does not provide financial, tax, or legal advice.</strong> The information is
    provided for general informational purposes only. The calculations, results, and content do not
    constitute professional advice of any kind. For advice specific to your circumstances, consult
    HMRC, a chartered accountant, or a qualified tax advisor. We recommend verifying results via the
    official HMRC tax calculator.
  </p>

  <h2>4. Privacy and Data Protection</h2>
  <p>
    All calculations are performed entirely in your browser using client-side JavaScript. No salary
    data, tax code selections, or other personal financial information is transmitted to our servers.
    We use Plausible Analytics, a privacy-friendly service that uses no cookies and is fully UK GDPR
    compliant. See our full <a href="/privacy/">Privacy Policy</a> for details.
  </p>

  <h2>5. Cookies and Local Storage</h2>
  <p>
    This website uses no tracking cookies. No advertising, profiling, or third-party cookies are placed.
    User preferences (such as dark/light mode) are stored in the browser's localStorage, which is not a
    cookie and is never transmitted to our servers. Cloudflare may use a strictly necessary security
    cookie (__cf_bm) for bot detection. Since no tracking cookies are used, a cookie consent banner is
    not legally required under PECR.
  </p>

  <h2>6. Accuracy</h2>
  <p>
    We make every effort to keep rates and thresholds up to date with the latest HMRC publications.
    However, we cannot guarantee that all information is accurate, complete, or current at all times.
    Tax rates, thresholds, and allowances may change during a tax year. Use at your own risk and always
    verify with official sources.
  </p>

  <h2>7. User Responsibilities</h2>
  <p>
    Users agree to use this website in a lawful manner and in accordance with these terms. Users shall
    not: (a) use the website for any illegal or unauthorised purpose; (b) attempt to gain unauthorised
    access to any part of the website, its servers, or any connected systems; (c) reproduce, distribute,
    or modify any content without prior written authorisation; or (d) use automated systems to extract
    data from the website (scraping) without express permission.
  </p>

  <h2>8. Intellectual Property</h2>
  <p>
    All content, design, code, logos, calculation algorithms, and trademarks on this website are the
    property of Mottalib Radif and are protected by copyright under the Copyright, Designs and Patents
    Act 1988. Users may access and use the website for personal, non-commercial purposes only. Any other
    use requires prior written consent. Brief quotations for informational purposes are permitted
    provided the source is credited.
  </p>

  <h2>9. UK GDPR Rights</h2>
  <p>
    Under the UK GDPR and Data Protection Act 2018, you have the right to access, rectify, erase,
    restrict processing, data portability, object to processing, and withdraw consent at any time.
    Since no personal data is collected through our calculators, these rights are satisfied by default.
    You have the right to lodge a complaint with the Information Commissioner's Office (ICO) at
    <a href="https://ico.org.uk" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">ico.org.uk</a>. For enquiries, contact
    us at contact@realsalary.co.uk.
  </p>

  <h2>10. Limitation of Liability</h2>
  <p>
    To the fullest extent permitted by law, {SITE_NAME} and its operators shall not be liable for any
    direct, indirect, incidental, consequential, or punitive damages arising from the use of or inability
    to use this website, including but not limited to damages resulting from reliance on calculation
    results or informational content. The website is provided on an "as is" and "as available" basis
    without warranties of any kind, express or implied.
  </p>
  <p>
    The publisher is not responsible for data loss, service interruptions, or damages to user equipment
    resulting from the use of the website.
  </p>

  <h2>11. External Links</h2>
  <p>
    This site may contain links to external websites, including gov.uk, HMRC, and other authoritative
    sources. The publisher has no control over the content of these sites and disclaims all responsibility
    for their content, privacy practices, or availability.
  </p>

  <h2>12. Governing Law</h2>
  <p>
    These terms are governed by and construed in accordance with the laws of England and Wales. Any
    disputes arising from the use of this website shall be subject to the exclusive jurisdiction of the
    courts of England and Wales, after any attempt at amicable resolution. The potential invalidity of
    any clause shall not affect the remaining provisions.
  </p>

  <h2>13. Changes and Contact</h2>
  <p>
    We may update these terms at any time. Continued use of the site constitutes acceptance of the
    current terms. For questions, contact us at:<br />
    Email: <a href="mailto:contact@realsalary.co.uk">contact@realsalary.co.uk</a>
  </p>
</GuideLayout>
